    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Gore Failed to Stop Harmful Oil Pipeline Law</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert F LaPorta letter comments on June 22 editorial warning against dangers of greenhouse gas emissions (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You warn (editorial, June 22) of the dangers if we do not reduce greenhouse gas emissions. As you say, one-third of these gases are produced by electric power plants. While conservation and renewable resources may help, if we wish to maintain our living standard, we must again consider nuclear energy. It produces no greenhouse gases, and nuclear waste can be safely handled and stored.</p>
        <p>ROBERT F. LAPORTA  Dix Hills, N.Y., June 22, 1997</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
